ATTRIBUTION NOTICE

This software is based on the mining method selection methodology described in:

1. Nicholas, D.E. (1981). "Method Selection â€“ A Numerical Approach."
   Design and Operation of Caving and Sublevel Stoping Mines, Chapter 4,
   pp. 39-53.

2. Miller-Tait, L., Pakalnis, R. and Poulin, R. (1995). "UBC Mining Method
   Selection." 4th International Symposium on Mine Planning & Equipment
   Selection, Calgary, Oct 31-Nov 3, 1995, pp. 163-168.

The scoring weights used in this software were extracted from the UBC Mining
Method Selector Excel spreadsheet (v1.1.0) implemented by Jeff Breadner (1999).

This is an open-source reimplementation and is NOT an official product of the
University of British Columbia (UBC) or the original authors. No endorsement
by UBC or the original authors is claimed or implied.

DISCLAIMER

This software is provided for educational and preliminary screening purposes
only. Results should not be used as the sole basis for engineering decisions.
Professional engineering judgment and detailed feasibility studies are required
for actual mining method selection. The authors and contributors make no
warranties about the accuracy, completeness, or suitability of this software
for any particular purpose.
